    DSM 
    
    sprint retrospective
       A sprint retrospective is a meeting held at the end of a sprint in Agile project management, specifically within the Scrum framework. It's a dedicated time for the development team to reflect on the past sprint, identify what went well, what didn't, and what can be improved in the next sprint. This process is crucial for continuous improvement and optimizing team performanc